FBIS4-58065 "drnes084_j_94021" FBIS-NES-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' Defense Ministry Details Clashes JN3004211594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 2000 GMT 30 Apr 94 JN3004211594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Excerpt] An official military source at the command of the Defense Ministry [word indistinct] has stated the following to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA': Separatist elements in the Yemeni Socialist Party rebelling against Constitutional legitimacy have consistently issued fabricated [word indistinct] in the name of the Defense Ministry in which it (?changes) facts and spreads venom and spite and information at variance with what happened at 'Imran Camp on Wedensday and Thursday [27, 28 April] about the regrettable infighting [words indistinct] the armed forces and security. Out of our concern to present the whole truth to our Yemeni masses, we would like to state the following: First, at 1400 on Wednesday, 27 April, bloody fighting erupted at 'Imran camp with heavy fire coming from the 3d Armored Brigade directed at the mess in the camp [word indistinct] the Military Committee with the participation of the American and French military attaches (?was convening a meeting). The fire was also directed at [word indistinct] the 1st Armored Brigade and [word indistinct] its concentrations including [word indistinct] concentrations, including the commander of the camp launching tank missiles [words indistinct] [passage omitted]
